-- ============================================================
-- SPAWN COMPOSITION CONFIGURATION
-- ============================================================
--
-- PURPOSE
--   Defines what "easy" and "hard" compositions mean for each
--   spawn system. Every composition tier maps to a Unit_Types
--   key (defined later in this file) so you can see — and edit —
--   the exact units that will appear.
--
-- HOW THE SYSTEM CONNECTS
--   ┌─────────────────────────────┐
--   │  difficulty.scar            │  ← You pick a tier value
--   │  e.g. patrol_strength       │    ("easy" or "hard")
--   │  e.g. phase2_spawn_tier     │
--   └──────────┬──────────────────┘
--              │ tier string
--              ▼
--   ┌─────────────────────────────┐
--   │  THIS TABLE                 │  ← Tier string maps to a
--   │  Spawn_Compositions         │    Unit_Types key
--   └──────────┬──────────────────┘
--              │ Unit_Types key
--              ▼
--   ┌─────────────────────────────┐
--   │  Unit_Types table           │  ← Actual unit list with
--   │  (further below in this     │    {type, numSquads} entries
--   │   file, search "Unit_Types")│
--   └─────────────────────────────┘
--
-- HOW TO EDIT UNIT COMPOSITIONS
--   Step 1: Find the spawn group you want to change below.
--   Step 2: Note the "unit_types_key" value (e.g. "units_camp_easy").
--   Step 3: Search this file for that key inside "Unit_Types = {".
--   Step 4: Change {type, numSquads} entries to adjust units.
--
--   Example — make easy patrols stronger:
--     1. Find patrol.easy below → unit_types_key = "units_camp_easy"
--     2. Search for "units_camp_easy" in the Unit_Types table
--     3. Change: {type = "scar_spearman", numSquads = 7}
--        To:     {type = "scar_spearman", numSquads = 12}
--     4. Save and test in-game.
--
-- RELATED FILES
--   difficulty.scar  → Per-tier toggles & tier strings (DC.*)
--   spawns.scar      → Wave scheduling, timing, spawn markers
--   THIS FILE        → Composition definitions + Unit_Types
--
-- ============================================================

